I suggest you go forward with the version numbering. 

1.99.0 --> 1.99.1 

At the next release your package will have 2.0.0. Take a look at the version numbering document  http://bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/version-numbering/.

Make the changes you need to and go to version number 1.99.1. This is the most straightforward way to deal with the problem at hand.

Best,

