Subject: [Bioc-devel] New Package and New Docker Image Submission Deadline
 for Bioc Release 3.11
Message-ID: <MN2PR12MB40775ECEF4DAC048E08F7998F9FA0@MN2PR12MB4077.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The final day to submit new packages and new docker images to the Bioconductor contributions tracker to have a shot at being included in the upcoming 3.11 release is Friday April 3rd.

Please note: submission by this date does not guarantee it will be included - the package must undergo an official review and be accepted by Wednesday April 22nd.


Some guidelines can be found at the following links
New packages: http://bioconductor.org/developers/package-submission/
Docker Image Best Practices: https://github.com/Bioconductor/bioconductor_docker/blob/master/best_practices.md

The place to submit new package and docker images is: https://github.com/Bioconductor/Contributions


Submissions after Friday April 3rd and those that are not accepted by April 22nd will still be able to be in Bioconductor but will be included in the development branch until the 3.12 release in Fall.  Please do not expect rush or exceptions; reviews of packages submitted after Friday April 3rd will be time-dependent of the reviewer based on other pre-release preparation.

Please see the release schedule for other important deadlines.
http://bioconductor.org/developers/release-schedule

Cheers,
Bioconductor Core Team



