hi Paul,

regarding the question "should I eliminate every dependency I can?" and 
relating to what Martin mentioned in his email below about a discussion 
we had about dependencies. you can use the current devel version of 
'BiocPkgTools' to try to answer that question:

library(BiocPkgTools)

depdf <- buildPkgDependencyDataFrame(repo=c("CRAN", "BioCsoft"),
dependencies=c("Depends", "Imports"))

pkgDepMetrics("MotifDb", depdf)
 ??????????????? ImportedAndUsed Exported Usage DepOverlap DepGainIfExcluded
rtracklayer?????????????????? 1????? 131? 0.76 0.92??????????????? 23
IRanges?????????????????????? 7????? 254? 2.76 0.21???????????????? 0
S4Vectors???????????????????? 8????? 272? 2.94 0.18???????????????? 0
BiocGenerics????????????????? 9????? 139? 6.47 0.13???????????????? 0
splitstackshape????????????? NA?????? 16??? NA 0.05???????????????? 2
Biostrings?????????????????? NA????? 240??? NA 0.33???????????????? 0

these metrics try to summarize the dependency burden of 'MotifDb' and, 
for instance, you can see here that 'MotifDb' is apparently only using 
one function from 'rtracklayer' while a very high percentage of the 
dependencies of 'MotifDb' and 'rtracklayer' are the same, possibly 
implying that a large fraction of the dependency burden of 'MotifDb' 
comes from 'rtracklayer'. the last column points in that direction 
saying that if you get rid of 'rtracklayer', the 'MotifDb' package would 
have 23 fewer dependencies.

you can find more information about 'pkgDepMetrics()' and its output in 
its manual page and in the vignette of 'BiocPkgTools'.

cheers,

robert.

